Oh here is your problem:
```
File "/home/zeng/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/torch/init.py", line 311, in 
import torch.cuda
File "/home/zeng/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/torch/cuda/init.py", line 19, in 
from multiprocessing.util import register_after_fork as _register_after_fork
File "/home/zeng/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/multiprocessing/init.py", line 65, in 
from multiprocessing.util import SUBDEBUG, SUBWARNING
File "/home/zeng/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/multiprocessing/util.py", line 41, in 
from subprocess import _args_from_interpreter_flags
File "/home/zeng/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/subprocess.py", line 72, in 
import select <------ this here
File "/home/zeng/haha/select.py", line 1, in  
from torch.autograd import Variable  
```

Python's multiprocessing module imports select, and due to how Python import works, it imports your file rather than the actual select module. I don't think that we can do much here. Same thing happens if you have 
```
# math.py
print(1/0)

# console
import numpy
```
